msgctxt "sn35.127:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.127:0.2"
msgid "13. Gahapativagga "
msgstr "13. Householders "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn35.127:0.3"
msgid "127. Bhāradvājasutta "
msgstr "127. With Bhāradvāja "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.111, sc1
msgctxt "sn35.127:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā piṇḍolabhāradvājo kosambiyaṃ viharati ghositārāme. "
msgstr "At one time Venerable Piṇḍola Bhāradvāja was staying near Kosambi, in Ghosita’s Monastery. "

msgctxt "sn35.127:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho rājā udeno yenāyasmā piṇḍolabhāradvājo tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā piṇḍolabhāradvājena saddhiṃ sammodi. "
msgstr "Then King Udena went up to Piṇḍola Bhāradvāja and exchanged greetings with him. "

msgctxt "sn35.127:1.3"
msgid "Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho rājā udeno āyasmantaṃ piṇḍolabhāradvājaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side, and said to him: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: susū → susu (bj, mr)
msgctxt "sn35.127:1.4"
msgid "“ko nu kho, bho bhāradvāja, hetu ko paccayo yenime daharā bhikkhū susū kāḷakesā bhadrena yobbanena samannāgatā paṭhamena vayasā anikīḷitāvino kāmesu yāvajīvaṃ paripuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ caranti, addhānañca āpādentī”ti? "
msgstr "“Master Bhāradvāja, there are these young monks who are youthful, black-haired, blessed with youth, in the prime of life; and they’ve never played around with sensual pleasures. What is the cause, what is the reason why they practice the full and pure spiritual life as long as they live, maintaining it for a long time?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.127:1.5"
msgid "“Vuttaṃ kho etaṃ, mahārāja, tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena: "
msgstr "“Great king, this has been stated by the Blessed One, who knows and sees, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.127:1.6"
msgid "‘etha tumhe, bhikkhave, mātumattīsu mātucittaṃ upaṭṭhapetha, bhaginimattīsu bhaginicittaṃ upaṭṭhapetha, dhītumattīsu dhītucittaṃ upaṭṭhapethā’ti. "
msgstr "‘Please, monks, think of women your mother’s age as your mother. Think of women your sister’s age as your sister. And think of women your daughter’s age as your daughter.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.127:1.7"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho, mahārāja, hetu, ayaṃ paccayo yenime daharā bhikkhū susū kāḷakesā bhadrena yobbanena samannāgatā paṭhamena vayasā anikīḷitāvino kāmesu yāvajīvaṃ paripuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ caranti, addhānañca āpādentī”ti. "
msgstr "This is a cause, great king, this is a reason why these young monks practice the full and pure spiritual life as long as they live, maintaining it for a long time.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
#. VAR: Lolaṃ → loḷaṃ (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn35.127:2.1"
msgid "“Lolaṃ kho, bho bhāradvāja, cittaṃ. "
msgstr "“But Master Bhāradvāja, the mind is wanton. "

msgctxt "sn35.127:2.2"
msgid "Appekadā mātumattīsupi lobhadhammā uppajjanti, bhaginimattīsupi lobhadhammā uppajjanti, dhītumattīsupi lobhadhammā uppajjanti. "
msgstr "Sometimes thoughts of desire come up even for women your mother’s age, your sister’s age, or your daughter’s age. "

msgctxt "sn35.127:2.3"
msgid "Atthi nu kho, bho bhāradvāja, añño ca hetu, añño ca paccayo yenime daharā bhikkhū susū kāḷakesā … pe … addhānañca āpādentī”ti? "
msgstr "Is there another cause, another reason why these young monks live the full and pure spiritual life for their entire life?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.112, sc3
msgctxt "sn35.127:3.1"
msgid "“Vuttaṃ kho etaṃ, mahārāja, tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena: "
msgstr "“Great king, this has been stated by the Blessed One, who knows and sees, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.127:3.2"
msgid "‘etha tumhe, bhikkhave, imameva kāyaṃ uddhaṃ pādatalā adho kesamatthakā tacapariyantaṃ pūraṃ nānappakārassa asucino paccavekkhatha—"
msgstr "‘Please, monks, examine your own body up from the soles of the feet and down from the tips of the hairs, wrapped in skin and full of many kinds of filth. "

#. VAR: nhāru → nahāru (bj) | nahārū (s1-3, km) | naharu (pts1)
#. VAR: aṭṭhimiñjaṃ → aṭṭhimiñjā (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.127:3.3"
msgid "atthi imasmiṃ kāye kesā lomā nakhā dantā taco maṃsaṃ nhāru aṭṭhi aṭṭhimiñjaṃ vakkaṃ hadayaṃ yakanaṃ kilomakaṃ pihakaṃ papphāsaṃ antaṃ antaguṇaṃ udariyaṃ karīsaṃ pittaṃ semhaṃ pubbo lohitaṃ sedo medo assu vasā kheḷo siṅghāṇikā lasikā muttan’ti. "
msgstr "In this body there is head hair, body hair, nails, teeth, skin, flesh, sinews, bones, bone marrow, kidneys, heart, liver, diaphragm, spleen, lungs, intestines, mesentery, undigested food, feces, bile, phlegm, pus, blood, sweat, fat, tears, grease, saliva, snot, synovial fluid, urine.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.127:3.4"
msgid "Ayampi kho, mahārāja, hetu, ayaṃ paccayo yenime daharā bhikkhū susū kāḷakesā … pe … addhānañca āpādentī”ti. "
msgstr "This is also a cause, great king, this is a reason why these young monks live the full and pure spiritual life for their entire life, maintaining it for a long time.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.127:3.5"
msgid "“Ye te, bho bhāradvāja, bhikkhū bhāvitakāyā bhāvitasīlā bhāvitacittā bhāvitapaññā, tesaṃ taṃ sukaraṃ hoti. "
msgstr "“This is easy to do for those mendicants who have developed their physical endurance, ethics, mind, and wisdom. "

msgctxt "sn35.127:3.6"
msgid "Ye ca kho te, bho bhāradvāja, bhikkhū abhāvitakāyā abhāvitasīlā abhāvitacittā abhāvitapaññā, tesaṃ taṃ dukkaraṃ hoti. "
msgstr "But it’s hard to do for those mendicants who have not developed their physical endurance, ethics, mind, and wisdom. "

#. VAR: manasi karissāmīti → manasi karissāmāti (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
#. VAR: subhatova → subhato vā (bj) | subhato ca (s1, s2, km)
msgctxt "sn35.127:3.7"
msgid "Appekadā, bho bhāradvāja, asubhato manasi karissāmīti subhatova āgacchati. "
msgstr "Sometimes I plan to focus on something as ugly, but only its beauty comes to mind. "

msgctxt "sn35.127:3.8"
msgid "Atthi nu kho, bho bhāradvāja, añño ca kho hetu añño ca paccayo yenime daharā bhikkhū susū kāḷakesā … pe … addhānañca āpādentī”ti? "
msgstr "Is there another cause, another reason why these young monks live the full and pure spiritual life for their entire life?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn35.127:4.1"
msgid "“Vuttaṃ kho etaṃ, mahārāja, tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena: "
msgstr "“Great king, this has been stated by the Blessed One, who knows and sees, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.127:4.2"
msgid "‘etha tumhe, bhikkhave, indriyesu guttadvārā viharatha. "
msgstr "‘Please, monks, live with sense doors guarded. "

msgctxt "sn35.127:4.3"
msgid "Cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā mā nimittaggāhino ahuvattha, mānubyañjanaggāhino. "
msgstr "When you see a sight with your eyes, don’t get caught up in the features and details. "

msgctxt "sn35.127:4.4"
msgid "Yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ cakkhundriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ, tassa saṃvarāya paṭipajjatha. Rakkhatha cakkhundriyaṃ; cakkhundriye saṃvaraṃ āpajjatha. "
msgstr "If the faculty of sight were left unrestrained, bad unskillful qualities of desire and aversion would become overwhelming. For this reason, practice restraint, protect the faculty of sight, and achieve its restraint. "

msgctxt "sn35.127:4.5"
msgid "Sotena saddaṃ sutvā … pe … "
msgstr "When you hear a sound with your ears … "

msgctxt "sn35.127:4.6"
msgid "ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā … "
msgstr "When you smell an odor with your nose … "

msgctxt "sn35.127:4.7"
msgid "jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā … "
msgstr "When you taste a flavor with your tongue … "

msgctxt "sn35.127:4.8"
msgid "kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā … "
msgstr "When you feel a touch with your body … "

msgctxt "sn35.127:4.9"
msgid "manasā dhammaṃ viññāya mā nimittaggāhino ahuvattha, mānubyañjanaggāhino. "
msgstr "When you know a thought with your mind, don’t get caught up in the features and details. "

msgctxt "sn35.127:4.10"
msgid "Yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ manindriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ, tassa saṃvarāya paṭipajjatha. Rakkhatha manindriyaṃ; manindriye saṃvaraṃ āpajjathā’ti. "
msgstr "If the faculty of mind were left unrestrained, bad unskillful qualities of desire and aversion would become overwhelming. For this reason, practice restraint, protect the faculty of mind, and achieve its restraint.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.127:4.11"
msgid "Ayampi kho, mahārāja, hetu ayaṃ paccayo yenime daharā bhikkhū susū kāḷakesā bhadrena yobbanena samannāgatā paṭhamena vayasā anikīḷitāvino kāmesu yāvajīvaṃ paripuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ caranti, addhānañca āpādentī”ti. "
msgstr "This is also a cause, great king, this is a reason why these young monks practice the full and pure spiritual life as long as they live, maintaining it for a long time.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.113, sc5
msgctxt "sn35.127:5.1"
msgid "“Acchariyaṃ, bho bhāradvāja; abbhutaṃ, bho bhāradvāja. "
msgstr "“It’s incredible, Master Bhāradvāja, it’s amazing! "

#. VAR: Yāva subhāsitañcidaṃ → yāva subhāsitamidaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "sn35.127:5.2"
msgid "Yāva subhāsitañcidaṃ, bho bhāradvāja, tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena. "
msgstr "How well this was said by the Buddha! "

# NOTE: Note the shift from the pi to va here. The king thinks the other reasons are dubious, but is convinced by this one, as it agrees with his experience.
msgctxt "sn35.127:5.3"
msgid "Esova kho, bho bhāradvāja, hetu, esa paccayo yenime daharā bhikkhū susū kāḷakesā bhadrena yobbanena samannāgatā paṭhamena vayasā anikīḷitāvino kāmesu yāvajīvaṃ paripuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ caranti, addhānañca āpādentīti. "
msgstr "This is the real cause, this is the reason why these young monks practice the full and pure spiritual life as long as they live, maintaining it for a long time. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: Ahampi kho, bho → ahampi bho (si, pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.127:5.4"
msgid "Ahampi kho, bho bhāradvāja, yasmiṃ samaye arakkhiteneva kāyena, arakkhitāya vācāya, arakkhitena cittena, anupaṭṭhitāya satiyā, asaṃvutehi indriyehi antepuraṃ pavisāmi, ativiya maṃ tasmiṃ samaye lobhadhammā parisahanti. "
msgstr "For sometimes I too enter the harem with unprotected body, speech, mind, mindfulness, and sense faculties. At those times powerful thoughts of desire get the better of me. "

msgctxt "sn35.127:5.5"
msgid "Yasmiñca khvāhaṃ, bho bhāradvāja, samaye rakkhiteneva kāyena, rakkhitāya vācāya, rakkhitena cittena, upaṭṭhitāya satiyā, saṃvutehi indriyehi antepuraṃ pavisāmi, na maṃ tathā tasmiṃ samaye lobhadhammā parisahanti. "
msgstr "But sometimes I enter the harem with protected body, speech, mind, mindfulness, and sense faculties. At those times such thoughts of desire don’t get the better of me. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.127:5.6"
msgid "Abhikkantaṃ, bho bhāradvāja, abhikkantaṃ, bho bhāradvāja. "
msgstr "Excellent, Master Bhāradvāja! Excellent! "

#. VAR: nikkujjitaṃ → nikujjitaṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.127:5.7"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bho bhāradvāja, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā vivareyya, mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya: ‘cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti; evamevaṃ bhotā bhāradvājena anekapariyāyena dhammo pakāsito. "
msgstr "As if he were righting the overturned, or revealing the hidden, or pointing out the path to the lost, or lighting a lamp in the dark so people with good eyes can see what’s there, Master Bhāradvāja has made the teaching clear in many ways. "

msgctxt "sn35.127:5.8"
msgid "Esāhaṃ, bho bhāradvāja, taṃ bhagavantaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi, dhammañca, bhikkhusaṃghañca. "
msgstr "I go for refuge to the Buddha, to the teaching, and to the mendicant Saṅgha. "

msgctxt "sn35.127:5.9"
msgid "Upāsakaṃ maṃ bhavaṃ bhāradvājo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti. "
msgstr "From this day forth, may Master Bhāradvāja remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.127:5.10"
msgid "Catutthaṃ. "
msgstr ""

